snippet.textDisplay: is it weird that we live in a society that is focused and ran on the whole concept of "making money" I'm not saying money doesn't make the world go around but I feel like humans are the most selfish and self centred creatures ever. How can we enjoy a life of our own knowing that there are people struggling in many ways shapes and forms because of the whole concept and idea of "money" I acknowledge the fact that matt has worked hard and come up from the bottom to now running a multi million dollar and multi national company but I can't help get a weird vibe when all they talk about is making money and other people trying to make money like that's there sole focus and purpose. How about we all focus on helping people by making the world a better place by making yourself a better person to start off with. At the end of the day, do we really care about buying "things" and materialistic objects for the benefit of ourselves? Sure its great to get a new laptop, new game, new car... even some nice food. But how about we take a thought for people who can't eat food and can't buy new "things" for their own little selfish happiness. Im not saying it's anyones fault and we shouldn't care for ourselves but I find it disturbing how the whole world is ran/running currently and I think the only way to change it is by trying to change individually and spread the message that caring for yourself may not be the right answer when others need it more.
